summary: Obsoletes conflict — foo-ng must be replaced by artifact foo
description: |
  System repo: foo-1.4 (baseline)
  Pre-installed: foo-ng-1.4 (Provides: foo, Obsoletes: foo < 3.0-1)
  Artifacts: foo-1.1

  foo-ng-1.4 satisfies the foo require via virtual provides, so the
  presence check skips installation.  verify-installation then fails
  because the installed provider (foo-ng) did not come from the artifact
  repository.  The fix requires --allowerasing so that foo-ng is removed
  and foo-1.1 is installed from the artifact.

context+:
  verified_artifact: foo-1.1
  xfail: "true"

environment+:
  PRE_INSTALLED_PACKAGE: rpms/foo-ng-1.4/foo-ng-1.4*.rpm
  EXPECTED_PACKAGE: foo-1.1
